```json
{
  "application": "lammps",
  "details": {
    "partition": "gpu-geforce",
    "nodes": 1,
    "gpus": 1,
    "nodelist": "gpu-200-4",
    "job_name": "step-7",
    "executable": "/home/yfwang09/Codes/lammps/src/lmp_icc_serial",
    "input_file": "/home/yfwang09/Codes/MLmat/MetallicGlass/data/natom-5000/qrate-1.0e+10/sample_0/lammps_scripts/in.7",
    "flags": "-sf gpu -pk gpu 1"
  }
}
```

**Explanation:**

* **Application:** The script is running the LAMMPS molecular dynamics simulation software.
* **Details:**
    * The script uses the "gpu-geforce" partition and requests one node with one GPU.
    * It specifies the node "gpu-200-4" and names the job "step-7".
    * The executable path is `/home/yfwang09/Codes/lammps/src/lmp_icc_serial`.
    * The input script for the simulation is `/home/yfwang09/Codes/MLmat/MetallicGlass/data/natom-5000/qrate-1.0e+10/sample_0/lammps_scripts/in.7`.
    * The flags "-sf gpu -pk gpu 1" are used to specify GPU-accelerated simulations with one process per GPU.
